        <name>7.3.4.4 Exercise 4</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;p class="HELM_exercise"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Using any of the properties of determinants to minimise the arithmetic, evaluate the following determinant:&lt;/p&gt;
\[\Delta=\begin{vmatrix} y+z &amp;amp; x+z &amp;amp; x+y \\ x &amp;amp; y &amp;amp; z \\ 1 &amp;amp; 1 &amp;amp; 1 \end{vmatrix}\]

&lt;p&gt;\(\Delta=\) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]&lt;/p&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>We are given the determinant: \[ \Delta=\begin{vmatrix} y+z &amp;amp; x+z &amp;amp; x+y \\ x &amp;amp; y &amp;amp; z \\ 1 &amp;amp; 1 &amp;amp; 1 \end{vmatrix}.\]&lt;br&gt;The sum of the first and second rows is the row matrix \(\begin{bmatrix}x+y+z &amp;amp; x+y+z &amp;amp; x+y+z\end{bmatrix}\), which is \(x+y+z\) times the third row. Therefore the determinant is zero, by Properties 4 and 5.</generalfeedback>
